	<body>
		{{> header}}
		
		<div style = "text-align:left">
				<div style="font-size:125%">
					<div style = "display: inline-block; text-align: center; color: #333;font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;">
								<div style = "text-align: left; font-size: 150%">
										<p> A Simple Plan </p> 
								</div>
											<p> Simple Sam was a simple man. <br>He lived each day by a simple plan.<br>
											Enjoy your life and live while you can.<br>
											Make each day count and take a stand.<br>

											Stand on the left or stand on the right,<br>
											Whichever one you think is right.<br>
											Live each day as if your last.<br>
											Life's too short and gone too fast.<br>
											<br>
											Source: <a href = "https://www.familyfriendpoems.com/poem/a-simple-plan "> A simple Plan </a></p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		
		<div style = "text-align:center;">
				<div style="font-size:125%">
					<div style = "display: inline-block; text-align: left; color: #333;font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;">
								<div style = "text-align: left; font-size: 150%">
										<p> The Opposite is also True </p> 
								</div>
								<p>They say it's sweet that we laugh <br>
								because our bodies literally<br>
								can't contain the joy.<br>

								But the opposite is also true. We cry <br>
								because our bodies physically<br>
								can't contain the pain.<br>
								<br>
								Source: <a href = "https://www.familyfriendpoems.com/poem/the-opposite-is-also-true"> The opposite is true </a></p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		{{> footer}}
	</body>
